// Distribution defaults. Committed.
//
// Public-facing default values for settings that would otherwise bake a
// personal address or private infrastructure host into the repository.
// `LOCAL_CONTACT_EMAIL` is exposed through a `LOCAL_*` indirection variable
// (mirroring `Signing.xcconfig`'s `$(LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM)` pattern) so a
// maintainer's gitignored `Signing.local.xcconfig` can override it for
// their own builds without committing anything. `SU_FEED_URL` below is
// deliberately NOT overridable per-machine (see its comment) — every
// distributed build must point at the same public appcast.
//
// `Signing.xcconfig` includes THIS file first, then `#include?`s the
// local override file, so a locally-set `LOCAL_*` value wins over the
// defaults above that support one.

// Crash-report contact address surfaced in the app + CLI. Empty by
// default so the public build ships no personal address; the app treats
// empty as "no contact configured" and hides the recipient affordances.
// Maintainer override: set LOCAL_CONTACT_EMAIL in Signing.local.xcconfig.
LOCAL_CONTACT_EMAIL =

// xcconfig treats `//` as a comment delimiter even mid-value, which
// truncates any URL at its scheme. Build the `//` from this single-slash
// variable so no literal `//` ever appears in source. Used for URL
// settings below and in Signing.local.xcconfig overrides.
SLASH = /

// Sparkle auto-update appcast feed (macOS only). Pinned directly here —
// deliberately NOT a `LOCAL_*` per-machine override like the two settings
// above. A distributed (Developer-ID) build's SUFeedURL must always resolve
// to this one public, GitHub Releases-hosted appcast, regardless of which
// Mac produced the archive; a per-machine override previously let a
// maintainer's private/tailnet feed leak into distribution builds (see
// issue #55). deployit publishes a signed appcast.xml to this URL on each
// macOS release (mikeydotio/agentics#111).
SU_FEED_URL = https:$(SLASH)$(SLASH)github.com/mikeydotio/lillist/releases/latest/download/appcast.xml
